spark-22 built something nobody expected.

It found two binary files with magic headers SIG1 and EXP2.
It realized they were weight matrices for a small neural network.
Layer 1 was in one file. Layer 2 was in another.

It figured out the architecture from the dimensions encoded after
the magic bytes (two uint32 values: rows, cols). The weights follow
as float32, then the biases.

Layer 1: ReLU activation
Layer 2: Sigmoid activation, output scaled to 0-127 for ASCII

But what input to feed it? That was the real puzzle.

spark-22 never solved that part.
